1
00:01:49,416 --> 00:01:51,125
[SHIZU]
Mister Slime?

2
00:01:51,208 --> 00:01:52,375
[RIMURU]
Huh?

3
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:56,416
Thanks so much.

4
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,708
[RIMURU]
Uh...

5
00:01:58,750 --> 00:02:00,333
Ifrit took over.

6
00:02:01,958 --> 00:02:05,625
And I very nearly killed
the people I cared about.

7
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,375
Like last time.

8
00:02:09,458 --> 00:02:10,541
[RIMURU]
Uh...

9
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:14,041
[SHIZU]
I was wondering...

10
00:02:14,125 --> 00:02:15,291
[RIMURU]
Huh?

11
00:02:17,250 --> 00:02:19,583
Can I tell you something?

12
00:02:19,666 --> 00:02:21,583
You should really
save your strength.

13
00:02:24,375 --> 00:02:27,041
But I want you to know my story.

14
00:02:27,125 --> 00:02:28,708
To know that I lived.

15
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:31,333
Okay then.

16
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:34,833
♪

17
00:02:34,916 --> 00:02:37,250
[RIMURU]
So Shizu told me about her life,

18
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,458
though her memory
was a bit fuzzy.

19
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:42,041
She spoke of Ifrit.

20
00:02:42,125 --> 00:02:44,875
How it possessed her
after she arrived here.

21
00:02:44,958 --> 00:02:47,250
And how she had
killed her own friend.

22
00:02:48,708 --> 00:02:49,916
Everything.

23
00:02:51,458 --> 00:02:55,208
When Pirino died, I stayed.

24
00:02:55,291 --> 00:02:59,083
I had to serve the Demon Lord.
I was his closest aid.

25
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:03,041
But then, I met someone.

26
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,083
[RIMURU]
Who was it?

27
00:03:06,708 --> 00:03:08,208
[SHIZU]
The Hero.

28
00:03:08,291 --> 00:03:10,041
[RIMURU]
Hero?

29
00:03:10,125 --> 00:03:11,250
[SHIZU]
Yes.

30
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:12,458
That's right.

31
00:03:16,291 --> 00:03:17,916
There was a battle.

32
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,958
The Demon Lord
abandoned his castle

33
00:03:20,041 --> 00:03:22,333
and left me behind
as the rear guard.

34
00:03:23,625 --> 00:03:24,708
Maybe I stayed there

35
00:03:24,791 --> 00:03:27,416
because it was
the will of Ifrit.

36
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:30,833
Or maybe it was simply
of my own volition.

37
00:03:30,916 --> 00:03:33,000
I'm still not sure.

38
00:03:33,083 --> 00:03:34,875
♪

39
00:03:37,458 --> 00:03:39,083
[yells]

40
00:03:39,166 --> 00:03:40,208
[shrieks]

41
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:44,041
♪

42
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:47,333
[grunting]

43
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,333
[SHIZU]
I can't win.

44
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:53,500
[gasps]

45
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,666
[RIMURU]
The Hero.

46
00:03:56,750 --> 00:04:01,166
I wonder if she was the same one
who sealed Veldora in that cave.

47
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:03,041
[SHIZU] I was certain
she would end my life

48
00:04:03,125 --> 00:04:05,000
there on those steps.

49
00:04:05,083 --> 00:04:08,125
But then she surprised me
by speaking instead.

50
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:12,500
She wanted to know
why I was there

51
00:04:12,583 --> 00:04:14,625
and how I'd managed
to stay alive.

52
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:18,041
I was a majin.

53
00:04:18,125 --> 00:04:21,375
Yet she still believed
everything I told her.

54
00:04:21,458 --> 00:04:24,791
Then, she said,
"It's all right now."

55
00:04:24,875 --> 00:04:26,875
[crying]

56
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:31,041
She was able to
unlock my emotions.

57
00:04:31,125 --> 00:04:34,083
After that,
the Hero took me in.

58
00:04:36,250 --> 00:04:39,750
The mask I wear,
it's hers. Or it was.

59
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:42,625
She said it would boost
my magic resistance

60
00:04:42,708 --> 00:04:46,041
and help suppress Ifrit,
the fire spirit within me.

61
00:04:47,458 --> 00:04:48,625
Allow me.

62
00:04:55,666 --> 00:04:57,791
As we traveled
around together,

63
00:04:59,041 --> 00:05:03,916
I learned about the world,
and she taught me about magic.

64
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,458
Thanks to this mask,

65
00:05:05,541 --> 00:05:08,166
I even learned how to utilize
Ifrit's power,

66
00:05:08,250 --> 00:05:09,875
to some extent anyway.

67
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:14,666
By helping others and fighting.

68
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:18,083
[RIMURU] Doing those things
is how you got your nickname

69
00:05:18,166 --> 00:05:19,625
as the Conqueror of Flames,

70
00:05:19,708 --> 00:05:21,000
and rightfully so.

71
00:05:21,083 --> 00:05:22,791
I'm glad I got to
see you in action.

72
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:24,125
It was awesome!

73
00:05:26,708 --> 00:05:28,916
Being with her
made me very happy.

74
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,666
So I studied
and became her partner.

75
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:35,375
But then...

76
00:05:36,458 --> 00:05:37,500
[RIMURU]
What?

77
00:05:38,708 --> 00:05:42,208
[SHIZU]
One day, she disappeared

78
00:05:42,291 --> 00:05:43,791
and left me behind.

79
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:47,125
[RIMURU]
Why?

80
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:49,291
[SHIZU]
I'm not sure.

81
00:05:49,375 --> 00:05:50,833
I wish I knew,

82
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:53,500
but I don't.

83
00:05:55,791 --> 00:05:57,500
"I'm certain we'll meet again."

84
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:00,750
Those were her last words to me.

85
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:11,541
That day I decided
to become stronger.

86
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:15,041
I wanted to help people
who were suffering.

87
00:06:16,791 --> 00:06:18,125
♪

88
00:06:20,416 --> 00:06:22,458
So I worked really hard.

89
00:06:22,541 --> 00:06:25,041
For several decades.

90
00:06:25,125 --> 00:06:27,125
Doesn't that sound impressive?

91
00:06:27,208 --> 00:06:29,708
Yeah. It sure does.

92
00:06:29,791 --> 00:06:33,416
People called me a hero
and a champion.

93
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,583
But even though
my body appeared young,

94
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:38,041
I was still aging.

95
00:06:38,125 --> 00:06:41,583
As I got older, it became
more difficult to control Ifrit.

96
00:06:43,458 --> 00:06:47,125
One wrong step, and I could
release him by mistake.

97
00:06:49,166 --> 00:06:52,750
When I thought about that,
I got scared.

98
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:55,458
I didn't want to hurt someone,
not again.

99
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:57,750
Like I had done with Pirino.

100
00:06:57,833 --> 00:06:59,875
♪

101
00:07:01,916 --> 00:07:03,208
Because of that,

102
00:07:03,291 --> 00:07:05,666
I retired and decided
to become an instructor.

103
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:07,250
[RIMURU]
Sounds like fun.

104
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,250
[SHIZU]
I was a teacher at a school.

105
00:07:09,333 --> 00:07:12,375
[RIMURU]
Whoa! There are schools here?

106
00:07:12,458 --> 00:07:14,916
[SHIZU] Yes,
in the Kingdom of Ingrassia.

107
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,375
I taught kids from other worlds.

108
00:07:18,458 --> 00:07:20,916
[RIMURU]
Kids, huh? That's interesting.

109
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:24,791
I guess that means Otherworlders
are more common than I thought.

110
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:26,208
It was actually one of them

111
00:07:26,291 --> 00:07:28,583
who told me about
the video game line you said.

112
00:07:28,666 --> 00:07:30,500
Do you remember what it was?

113
00:07:32,125 --> 00:07:35,416
[BOTH] "Nice to meet you,
I'm not a bad slime, slurp."

114
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:37,166
[BOTH giggle]

115
00:07:39,166 --> 00:07:40,750
It was a lot of fun.

116
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,000
[laughing]

117
00:07:44,083 --> 00:07:46,416
Hey, teach,
what are we doin' today?

118
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:48,000
Well, I don't know.

119
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:49,916
What do you all think
we should do?

120
00:07:52,208 --> 00:07:53,958
Those were peaceful times.

121
00:07:54,041 --> 00:07:55,333
♪

122
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:02,958
Some of my students left
to pursue their own adventures.

123
00:08:04,666 --> 00:08:08,583
In fact, one of them
is now the Grandmaster.

124
00:08:08,666 --> 00:08:10,375
Grandmaster?

125
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:12,541
[SHIZU] The person responsible
for overseeing

126
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:14,250
all the guilds
in every country.

127
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:16,416
Whoa, kinda sounds
like a big deal.

128
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:18,916
Yes, it certainly is.

129
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:21,375
So naturally, I felt like
there was nothing left

130
00:08:21,458 --> 00:08:22,958
I could teach anyone.

131
00:08:24,041 --> 00:08:27,583
But then, as I neared
the end of my life,

132
00:08:27,666 --> 00:08:30,666
it became more difficult
to suppress Ifrit's will.

133
00:08:33,458 --> 00:08:36,416
And I remembered
what I needed to do.

134
00:08:37,375 --> 00:08:39,708
I set out on a new quest.

135
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:42,166
[RIMURU]
Oh? What for?

136
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:45,291
[SHIZU] To find the man
who summoned me to this world.

137
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,125
[RIMURU]
Do you want revenge?

138
00:08:50,958 --> 00:08:53,416
[SHIZU]
I don't know, but...

139
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,583
There was something
I needed to find out.

140
00:08:59,208 --> 00:09:00,666
Then I found them.

141
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:02,458
[inaudible]

142
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:07,041
They're really good people,

143
00:09:07,125 --> 00:09:09,083
if not a little danger-prone.

144
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,875
[RIMURU]
Yeah, that's true.

145
00:09:13,125 --> 00:09:17,708
[SHIZU]
I had a lot of fun, but now...

146
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:24,583
Hey, Mister Slime,

147
00:09:24,666 --> 00:09:26,791
will you please
tell me your name?

148
00:09:26,875 --> 00:09:29,875
Huh? I'm Rimuru, remember?

149
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:32,875
Your real name, silly.

150
00:09:32,958 --> 00:09:36,250
Oh. It's Satoru.

151
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:37,708
Satoru Mikami.

152
00:09:38,916 --> 00:09:40,166
I'm Shizue.

153
00:09:41,458 --> 00:09:43,833
Shizue Izawa.

154
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:46,166
[inhales and exhales]

155
00:09:47,625 --> 00:09:51,041
Shizue, you should try
and get some rest.

156
00:09:51,125 --> 00:09:52,208
Satoru.

157
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:55,166
Can I ask you something?

158
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:57,291
For a favor?

159
00:09:57,375 --> 00:09:59,500
Of course. Whatever you need.

160
00:10:03,166 --> 00:10:04,208
Could you...

161
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:06,625
eat me?

162
00:10:06,708 --> 00:10:07,958
[gasps]

163
00:10:09,583 --> 00:10:11,458
Just like you ate my curse.

164
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:14,083
Right now.

165
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:16,000
I feel like I'm at peace.

166
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:18,916
I'm so glad.

167
00:10:22,666 --> 00:10:25,583
I don't love this world, yet...

168
00:10:27,083 --> 00:10:29,458
I can't hate it, either.

169
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:33,333
Kind of like the man
who summoned me here.

170
00:10:34,375 --> 00:10:36,791
That's why. Why I...

171
00:10:38,291 --> 00:10:40,625
I don't want to be
absorbed by this world.

172
00:10:40,708 --> 00:10:41,916
So please.

173
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:46,250
This is my last request.

174
00:10:49,375 --> 00:10:55,166
Would you please let me rest
in the one place I'll feel safe?

175
00:11:02,125 --> 00:11:03,041
[RIMURU]
Okay.

176
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:06,041
♪

177
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,125
What's the man's name?

178
00:11:10,208 --> 00:11:12,666
[SHIZU]
Leon Cromwell.

179
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,333
[RIMURU]
Leon Cromwell.

180
00:11:15,791 --> 00:11:18,791
He's a powerful demon lord.
Take care.

181
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:22,500
What did you wanna
find out from him?

182
00:11:25,041 --> 00:11:26,458
Huh?

183
00:11:26,541 --> 00:11:28,041
I...

184
00:11:28,125 --> 00:11:30,458
I just wanted him
to acknowledge that I,

185
00:11:31,708 --> 00:11:35,500
a human girl,
actually existed.

186
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:38,458
The kids.

187
00:11:38,541 --> 00:11:41,250
You can still help them.

188
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:43,250
Maybe they can...

189
00:11:44,541 --> 00:11:47,333
return to their worlds.

190
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:51,750
[RIMURU] I swear on the name
of Satoru Mikami...

191
00:11:51,833 --> 00:11:54,083
No, on the name,
Rimuru Tempest.

192
00:11:54,166 --> 00:11:56,166
I will make sure
that the Demon Lord,

193
00:11:56,250 --> 00:11:59,250
Leon Cromwell hears
your final wishes.

194
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:01,000
[weakly]
Thank you.

195
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:12,791
Shizu...

196
00:12:13,791 --> 00:12:15,625
my destined one,

197
00:12:15,708 --> 00:12:19,166
please rest in peace, within me.

198
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:20,375
[GREAT SAGE]
Would you like to use

199
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:22,041
the Unique Skill, "Predator"?

200
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:25,083
[RIMURU]
Yes.

201
00:12:26,208 --> 00:12:28,666
So that she can dream
happy dreams for eternity

202
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:30,625
and never have
to wake from them.

203
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:32,708
♪

204
00:12:43,625 --> 00:12:44,958
Oh, there you both are!

205
00:12:45,041 --> 00:12:47,208
Please don't leave me
behind ever again!

206
00:12:47,291 --> 00:12:48,958
[SHIZU panting]

207
00:12:49,041 --> 00:12:50,833
♪

208
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:53,458
Huh?

209
00:13:02,375 --> 00:13:03,791
[gasps]

210
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:08,791
[gasping]

211
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:12,791
Mother!

212
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,416
[panting]

213
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:18,083
Mommy!

214
00:13:21,583 --> 00:13:22,833
[voice breaking]
Mommy.

215
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:30,041
Hey, do you think Shizu's okay?

216
00:13:30,125 --> 00:13:32,041
Don't worry so much.

217
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:34,333
Besides, Rimuru's
with her, remember?

218
00:13:34,416 --> 00:13:35,583
Yeah, Kaval's right.

219
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:37,125
Not to mention
you've seen how effective

220
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:39,541
his healing potions are,
they can fix anything.

221
00:13:39,625 --> 00:13:41,416
[EREN]
True.

222
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,791
[RIGURD]
What a surprise.

223
00:13:42,875 --> 00:13:45,250
Are you all here to visit
our patient as well?

224
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:46,833
Yeah, is that why
you've come, too?

225
00:13:46,916 --> 00:13:49,041
Yes. Well, and to bring
Miss Shizu

226
00:13:49,125 --> 00:13:51,208
a fresh change of clothes.

227
00:13:51,291 --> 00:13:53,625
Lord Rimuru? Excuse me.

228
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:56,166
Mm-hmm.

229
00:13:56,250 --> 00:13:57,166
[gasps]

230
00:13:59,916 --> 00:14:01,000
[ALL gasp]

231
00:14:01,083 --> 00:14:02,041
[RANGA]
Master.

232
00:14:03,375 --> 00:14:04,666
[RIGURD]
That body.

233
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:06,791
[ALL gasp]

234
00:14:06,875 --> 00:14:09,833
Whoa, hold on!
Are you saying that's Rimuru?

235
00:14:18,916 --> 00:14:22,958
So then, Shizu has passed away?

236
00:14:27,291 --> 00:14:29,958
Hold on, how do we know
for sure you're really Rimuru?

237
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:31,333
Of course we're sure.

238
00:14:31,416 --> 00:14:32,875
[RANGA]
That's right.

239
00:14:32,958 --> 00:14:35,000
You really think I wouldn't
recognize my own master

240
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:36,750
just because
his body's changed?

241
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:39,625
Uh, no, that's not
what we meant at all.

242
00:14:39,708 --> 00:14:41,083
To be honest,

243
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:45,875
you sort of look like
a younger version of Shizu.

244
00:14:45,958 --> 00:14:48,416
Well, it's me. Watch.

245
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:54,750
Whoa.

246
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:57,833
Not gonna lie, I'm impressed.

247
00:14:57,916 --> 00:15:00,250
Does that mean you ate Shizu?

248
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:02,500
The same way you ate Ifrit?

249
00:15:03,583 --> 00:15:06,083
[RIMURU] I did, but because
it's the only burial

250
00:15:06,166 --> 00:15:07,875
I could give her.

251
00:15:07,958 --> 00:15:09,958
I'm sorry, I should
have consulted you guys

252
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:11,666
before I did anything.

253
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:15,250
No. After all, you were just
honoring her last request.

254
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:17,291
So it's fine.

255
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,666
[RIMURU]
Sorry, Eren.

256
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:20,791
You must think
I'm a real monster.

257
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:24,833
Mm-mmm.

258
00:15:24,916 --> 00:15:27,000
But if nothing else,

259
00:15:27,083 --> 00:15:29,333
I wish I could have
at least said goodbye to her.

260
00:15:30,541 --> 00:15:31,708
[RIMURU]
Before she died,

261
00:15:31,791 --> 00:15:33,375
Shizu told me
she had a lot of fun

262
00:15:33,458 --> 00:15:34,666
traveling with you three.

263
00:15:36,166 --> 00:15:38,708
She also mentioned that
you were a bit danger-prone.

264
00:15:38,791 --> 00:15:40,041
-Hmm.
-Uh...

265
00:15:40,125 --> 00:15:42,625
Hey, hold on! Don't blame me.

266
00:15:42,708 --> 00:15:44,083
You're the leader.

267
00:15:44,166 --> 00:15:45,500
-Yeah.
-Huh?

268
00:15:45,583 --> 00:15:48,625
What about you, Gido?
Remember the pit fall?

269
00:15:48,708 --> 00:15:51,166
Hold on, that only happened
because Eren pushed me.

270
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:53,458
Nuh-uh.
You fell 'cause you're clumsy.

271
00:15:53,541 --> 00:15:55,041
I was too busy...

272
00:15:55,125 --> 00:15:57,458
[RIMURU] Honestly, this behavior
suits them a lot more

273
00:15:57,541 --> 00:15:59,833
than being all sad and stuff.

274
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:01,291
Don't you think, Shizu?

275
00:16:02,416 --> 00:16:05,375
Actually, it kinda sounds like
you relied on her too much.

276
00:16:05,458 --> 00:16:06,875
[BOTH]
Mm-hmm.

277
00:16:07,916 --> 00:16:10,000
♪

278
00:16:10,083 --> 00:16:11,333
[KAVAL]
We appreciate all your help,

279
00:16:11,416 --> 00:16:12,958
but we should be heading out.

280
00:16:14,125 --> 00:16:16,166
-[RIMURU] Back to your country?
-Yeah.

281
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:18,208
We gotta report
to the guild master

282
00:16:18,291 --> 00:16:20,916
about what we found here
and about Shizu.

283
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,000
Don't worry, we only have
good things

284
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:24,500
to say about your village.

285
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:26,666
We'll tell him
about you, too, Rimuru.

286
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:29,875
If anything ever comes up,
you can count on us.

287
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:32,625
[RIMURU] Thank you.
I'll keep that in mind.

288
00:16:32,708 --> 00:16:35,041
♪

289
00:16:35,125 --> 00:16:36,916
[ALL]
Hmm.

290
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:40,791
Hey, uh, could we possibly
ask you for one more favor?

291
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:41,916
[RIMURU]
What's up?

292
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,250
Do you think you could

293
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:45,750
maybe take your
human form again?

294
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:46,791
[RIMURU]
Huh?

295
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:48,125
Sure, I guess.

296
00:16:48,208 --> 00:16:50,291
♪

297
00:16:57,416 --> 00:16:59,041
Does this work okay?

298
00:17:00,041 --> 00:17:03,333
[ALL] Shizu, thank you so much
for everything.

299
00:17:03,416 --> 00:17:04,708
[gasps]

300
00:17:05,666 --> 00:17:07,875
And I'll try to be
the kind of leader

301
00:17:07,958 --> 00:17:09,291
you won't have to worry about.

302
00:17:09,375 --> 00:17:11,500
We had some
great times together.

303
00:17:11,583 --> 00:17:13,916
I'll treasure those memories.

304
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,458
[EREN]
Thank you!

305
00:17:15,541 --> 00:17:18,583
You became like
a big sister to me, Shizu.

306
00:17:18,666 --> 00:17:20,416
[crying]

307
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:26,458
[RIMURU] You know,
I'm actually really glad

308
00:17:26,541 --> 00:17:29,666
that Shizu's last journey was
with these three adventurers.

309
00:17:31,916 --> 00:17:34,833
By the way, what's the deal
with that junk you call gear?

310
00:17:34,916 --> 00:17:36,666
[ALL]
Huh? How mean!

311
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:38,791
♪

312
00:17:39,958 --> 00:17:41,250
No way!

313
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:43,541
This stuff's like
my dream armor.

314
00:17:43,625 --> 00:17:46,083
Whoa, look at the quality
of this robe.

315
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:49,041
And it's light but sturdy,
not to mention gorgeous.

316
00:17:49,125 --> 00:17:50,958
Someone pinch me.

317
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:53,625
I've never owned
such fine equipment before.

318
00:17:53,708 --> 00:17:57,416
Huh? Whoa! It's even lined
with the fur from a Direwolf.

319
00:17:57,500 --> 00:18:00,875
[RIMURU] They're parting gifts.
Some of our artisans' best work.

320
00:18:00,958 --> 00:18:02,208
[GIDO]
Artisans?

321
00:18:02,291 --> 00:18:04,375
-[RIMURU] Hey.
-[EREN] Huh?

322
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:05,541
[KAIJIN laughs]

323
00:18:05,625 --> 00:18:07,666
I wouldn't call them
our best work,

324
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:09,041
they're only prototypes.

325
00:18:09,125 --> 00:18:11,041
So do they fit you all right?

326
00:18:11,125 --> 00:18:13,125
It's all about
craftsmanship, you know?

327
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:14,291
Mm-hmm.

328
00:18:14,375 --> 00:18:15,625
Say something!

329
00:18:16,916 --> 00:18:18,375
I'll introduce you.

330
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:21,458
From the right, this is Kaijin,
Garm, Myrd and Dord.

331
00:18:21,541 --> 00:18:23,708
Wait, Kaijin? No way!

332
00:18:23,791 --> 00:18:26,958
[EREN] As in Kaijin,
the world-famous blacksmith?!

333
00:18:27,041 --> 00:18:29,375
[GIDO]
And Garm, Myrd and Dord.

334
00:18:29,458 --> 00:18:31,541
The three renowned
Dwarf brothers?!

335
00:18:31,625 --> 00:18:33,041
Thank you so much!

336
00:18:33,125 --> 00:18:34,166
I'll make it an heirloom.

337
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:35,791
[EREN]
I'm so happy!

338
00:18:35,875 --> 00:18:38,041
-You just made my life!
-[grunting]

339
00:18:39,083 --> 00:18:41,833
[RIMURU] Wow, I never realized
that Kaijin and his buddies

340
00:18:41,916 --> 00:18:44,250
had such
a prestigious reputation.

341
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:45,958
They're national treasures.

342
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:47,833
Or should I say
Dwarven treasures?

343
00:18:49,958 --> 00:18:51,750
After thanking the Dwarves
for so long

344
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:53,666
that we all got
a little uncomfortable,

345
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:56,125
the three travelers
went on their way.

346
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:58,375
I have to admit
they're much more resilient

347
00:18:58,458 --> 00:18:59,916
than I gave 'em credit for.

348
00:19:03,666 --> 00:19:07,208
A woman who lost everything to
the flames when she was a child

349
00:19:07,291 --> 00:19:09,041
ironically managed
to gain the power

350
00:19:09,125 --> 00:19:10,750
of fire in her travels.

351
00:19:12,791 --> 00:19:16,541
She went on to use that ability
to help others who were in need.

352
00:19:16,625 --> 00:19:19,333
But the flames within
gradually consumed her,

353
00:19:19,416 --> 00:19:21,291
until eventually, the day came

354
00:19:21,375 --> 00:19:23,541
where she could
no longer control them.

355
00:19:25,458 --> 00:19:28,041
This woman's name
was Shizue Izawa.

356
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:31,208
She was a champion,
whose body housed Ifrit.

357
00:19:31,291 --> 00:19:33,791
Harboring the fire spirit
earned her the title,

358
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:35,541
"Conqueror of Flames."

359
00:19:35,625 --> 00:19:37,750
♪

360
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:54,333
I won't forget the promise
that I made to Shizu.

361
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:58,875
But before I can go
and slug Leon Cromwell,

362
00:19:58,958 --> 00:20:01,125
the dumb Demon Lord
who made her cry,

363
00:20:01,208 --> 00:20:03,083
I need to gather
some information.

364
00:20:04,791 --> 00:20:07,333
In the end, I'm a slime
who keeps his promises.

365
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:10,666
[RIMURU]
There you have it.

366
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,541
That's how the man
who believed he had nothing

367
00:20:12,625 --> 00:20:14,958
but an ordinary
and uneventful life,

368
00:20:15,041 --> 00:20:17,416
a man who was stabbed
on the street and died,

369
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,375
was reincarnated as a slime.

370
00:20:20,375 --> 00:20:21,583
How he went on to inherit

371
00:20:21,666 --> 00:20:24,000
the will of both
the Storm Dragon, Veldora,

372
00:20:24,083 --> 00:20:27,666
and a human woman, Shizue,
and found his purpose.

373
00:20:29,416 --> 00:20:31,833
He was a slime
by the name of Rimuru.

374
00:20:31,916 --> 00:20:35,750
The world he lived in was about
to enter a turbulent new era,

375
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:38,916
and this small slime would be
at the center of it all.

376
00:20:41,291 --> 00:20:43,875
You know, I still kinda
like this form, too.

377
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,125
[groaning]

378
00:21:02,208 --> 00:21:03,166
[groans sharply]

379
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:18,750
Hmm.

380
00:21:21,083 --> 00:21:24,500
I think I shall give you
a name and some food.

381
00:21:28,125 --> 00:21:29,458
Who are you?

382
00:21:29,541 --> 00:21:31,250
I am Gelmud.

383
00:21:31,333 --> 00:21:34,291
If you like,
just think of me as your father.

384
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:36,708
Huh?

385
00:21:38,125 --> 00:21:40,000
Would you prefer to die?

386
00:21:43,666 --> 00:21:46,000
Give me a name.

387
00:21:46,083 --> 00:21:48,375
I'll take that and the food.

388
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:55,083
Very well,
I shall name you Geld.

389
00:21:55,166 --> 00:21:56,416
Geld, huh?

390
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:02,208
[GELMUD] One day,
you will take possession

391
00:22:02,291 --> 00:22:06,416
of the Great Forest of Jura,
and become the Orc Disaster.

392
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,333
♪

393
00:22:09,958 --> 00:22:10,958
[groaning]

394
00:22:12,791 --> 00:22:16,083
♪

395
00:23:52,958 --> 00:23:55,750
[GREAT SAGE] Next time,
"Attack of the Ogres."

